  "response_text": "A small boy with dark brown hair sits sideways on a wooden bench outdoors in warm, golden light. He wears a green short-sleeved shirt, blue jeans, white socks, and sneakers. A fluffy pale-golden puppy lies across his lap, and the boy gently holds its head and strokes its ears. At the bottom of the picture, a small red-and-yellow Kodak logo appears beside the white script words “My best friend.” The boy looks down at the puppy with a quiet, absorbed expression, touching its muzzle and cheeks while the puppy gazes back at him.\n\nThe setting shifts to a rustic barn or shed area filled with straw and stacked hay bales. The boy, now wearing denim overalls over a plaid shirt, sits on the straw with the same golden puppy beside him. He holds an open picture book or magazine in front of his face, then lowers it as the puppy noses close. Chickens and a white duck move in the background and foreground. The boy sits with his back against a hay bale, surrounded by loose straw, and the puppy stands close enough to press its face against him. He reaches up and wraps his arms around the puppy’s neck in a hug, smiling as the dog leans into him.\n\nIn an autumn-colored outdoor pen, the boy stands in overalls among chickens and ducks, with a wire fence and bright orange leaves behind him. The puppy, now a little larger and sturdier, bounds in from the right and crouches playfully near a white duck. The boy watches calmly, hands at his sides, as the puppy sniffs and steps around the birds. The warm sunlight makes the leaves and straw glow, giving the scene a soft amber look.\n\nThe images blend into the boy running outside through tall grass with the pale puppy at his side. He wears a white baseball-style shirt with dark sleeves and a large red number “12” on the front, along with gray pants. The puppy trots in front of him, ears flopping and tail lifted, while the boy follows with arms slightly raised for balance. They move through a yard with trees and autumn foliage behind them. As they approach a house, a white porch railing and front steps come into view.\n\nOn the porch steps, the dog is now much larger, a golden retriever standing behind the boy near the doorway. The boy, wearing a light sweater with a patterned band across the chest and dark pants, steps down from the porch. A pumpkin sits near the bottom of the steps, and white decorative railings frame the porch. The big dog watches from behind him, alert and calm, as the boy comes forward with his arms out.\n\nA large Kodak film box then appears over the porch scene and takes over the picture. The box is bright yellow and orange with black accents. Readable text on it includes “Kodak PRINT FILM,” “Kodacolor VR film,” and a large “200.” It rests on a wooden surface, lit warmly, with the product name and speed number clearly displayed.\n\nThe commercial then returns to earlier memories in soft overlapping images: the boy sitting with the puppy on the bench, then the boy in the chicken pen with the dog and birds, then the child running with the puppy through the yard. These images visually connect the puppy growing into a full-sized golden retriever and the boy changing through different childhood moments.\n\nFinally, the boy stands on the porch steps facing the now full-grown golden retriever. He steps close and wraps his arms around the dog’s neck, hugging it tightly. The dog stands patiently beside the porch doorway, its golden coat catching the warm light. At the bottom of the image, the red-and-yellow Kodak logo appears again beside the white script words “Because time goes by.”",
